history.text: Hello.
Hello

There is this movie that, according to it's reviews is amazing called Catch Me If You can, it was an awesome staff like Leonardo Dicaprio and Tom Hanks and is about a kid who ends up becoming involved in cheque fraud and is so good at it the FBI ends up hiring him.
Have you seen it?  Did you enjoy it?

I have and it's really good.  Leo plays a character named Frank Abagnale Jr who is being chased by Carl Handly, played by Tom Hanks and he ends up preforming cons worth over $1000000 in free flights on Pan AM Airlines.
What did the critics think?
Well it got over 95% from Rotten Tomates and CimeaScore gave it an A- so it clearly was loved by critics
What was the best part?
Seeing him acting as a Pan American World Airlines Pilot was incredible.
Who was the director?
Steven Spielberg who is amazing as always
Yes, he is.  I love his movies
Did he get caught?

Did 
f

I don't remember but I think you'll love the part where after getting denied for a loan at a big bank, his father has to sell their large home and move into a small appartment.  But, Frank Abegnale Jr starts to catch on that his mom is cheating on his dad with her dads friend
Did
Did he blackmail him?

No, Leo's character actually takes off and runs away from home.  but he runs out of cash.  So he had to start posing as the pan am pilot and schaming the ckes.  HE ends up stealing close to $3 Million
How did he get caught?
Hmmm I'm not sure, but you have to imagine with Carly Handratty (played by Hanks) after you, it came down to good old fashion police work.
So what type of genre is it?
I remember Frank being flown home on a plane after being arrested and that's when Carl tells him that his dad died
Was it true?
Yeah, he escapes the plane to go and check.  And finds his mom with that guy she was having an affair with earlier
Was he hurt by the affair?
well right after seeing it, he notices his half sister and turns himself in, so was impacted in some way
Was he sentenced?
So he serves his sentence working for the FBI to help them
Did he show remorse?

Well he actually gets bored and tries to go board another plane as a pilot before Carl corners him and shows him noone is chasing him.  Carl lets him go and then Frank shows back up Monday morning to work
Why did Carl do that?
Couldn't tell you, but I know that right after the credits it shwoed that carl has been married for almost 30 years now and has three sons.
